  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skin on) into thin chips</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604316186213-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604316186213-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604316186213-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604316186213-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1604316186213-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and the <strong>dried sage</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15-20 min or until they are starting to brown – these are your <strong>festive fries</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604316202625-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604316202625-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604316202625-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604316202625-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1604316202625-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with a knob of<strong> butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk in your <strong>beef stock </strong>into the <strong>roux</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604316211461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604316211461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604316211461-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604316211461-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1604316211461-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chips and gravy are cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>beef mince</strong> to a bowl, season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and roll into 2 meatballs per person</p><p>Once the chips are starting to brown, push them to one side of the tray, add your <strong>smoked bacon </strong>to the other and return to the oven for 10-15 min or until the chips are crispy and the bacon is golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1604316224614-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1604316224614-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1604316224614-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1604316224614-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1604316224614-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong>, press them down firmly with a spatula to form a thin burger shape and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly charred on the bottom</p><p>Flip the <strong>burgers</strong> and top half with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and cook, covered, for 2-3 min further or until the burgers are cooked through and the cheese has melted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1604316278697-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1604316278697-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1604316278697-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1604316278697-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1604316278697-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the burgers are cooking, cut the ends off your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> and slice in half</p><p>Tip: Don’t chuck the crusts away. Instead, turn them into croutons!</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half</p><p>Add the<strong> ciabatta</strong> and <strong>brioche</strong> <strong>halves</strong> to a separate tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until toasted</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1604316304368-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1604316304368-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1604316304368-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1604316304368-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1604316304368-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once toasted, add the<strong> ciabatta</strong> to the <strong>gravy</strong> and set aside for 1-2 min or until it has started to soak up the gravy</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1604316347732-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1604316347732-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1604316347732-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1604316347732-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1604316347732-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread the <strong>brioche bases </strong>and<strong> lids</strong> with your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>cranberry sauce</strong></p><p>Top the <strong>brioche base</strong> with some<strong> shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> </strong>the<strong> cheesy beef patty</strong>,<strong> gravy-soaked ciabatta</strong>, <strong>remaining beef patty</strong>, <strong>crispy bacon</strong>, more<strong> shredded lettuce </strong>and the <strong>brioche lid</strong></p><p><strong>Skewer</strong> the burger and serve the<strong> festive fries</strong> and any <strong>remaining gravy</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
